COUSVINNYSACANUCK stalked the pace from the two path around the final turn then tipped out to three wide to give late effort to be up for the second place money. RUNTODAY went to the front to a pressured lead from the inside down the backstretch then vied for the lead around the final turn and tired. CODETOWIN tracked the leaders from off the rail around the first turn then steadily advanced from three wide to the top of the stretch, tipped out to four wide for a mild gain but bled and was vanned off. WISE ANCHOR raced off the pace on the inside to the three furlong marker and faded. GOTTA GO trailed the field and was not a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 2 5F Dirt CR: 67. Claiming Purse 25000. FOR FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 122 lbs.; , 123 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000. Louisiana Bred Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AMERICAN TSUNAMI co-led from three wide to the three furlong marker then edged away but was headed at the top of the stretch and matched strides with READY FOR THUNDER on the outside and AFRAID IM NOTCENTS on the inside down the stretch and won the nod. AFRAID IM NOTCENTS vied for the lead from the inside bumped with CONVALIDATION entering the turn and had to check slightly but made a rebid and matched strides with AMEARICAN TSUNAMI and READY FOR THUNDER but lost the photo. READY FOR THUNDER raced just off the pace to the turn then made a four wide bid at the quarter pole to engage the leader at the top of the stretch and took a narrow lead and fought gamely to deep stretch but was outfinished. JAYDYN CAT chased the leaders from close off the pace but lacked room on the turn and made a rebid into the stretch, angled out to four wide at the sixteenths pole but was no match for the top three. CONVALIDATION pressed the pace from the two path to the five sixteenths pole bumped AFRAID IM NOCENTS on the turn and tired. SHE'S EXTRA co-led from four wide to the three furlong marker and retreated. JOCKEY OBJECTION WAS POSTED, THE JOCKEY OF AFRAID IM NOTCENTS CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST AMERICAN TSUNAMI FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE ON THE TURN, AFTER A STEWARDS REVIEW NO ACTION WAS TAKEN AND THE CLAIM OF FOUL WAS DISALLOWED.
